{
  "texts": [
    "Generalizability (akin to external validity).",
    "The ability of an ML model to execute satisfactorily on new, independent cohorts across disparate populations, protocols, and deployment environments.",
    "When the model fails to meet this definition, it has learned biases.",
    "Lingering concerns center on too small datasets, restricted to single institutional/ regional sampling, exhibiting a population non-diversity, noise/artifacts, or variables in settings.",
    "Such datasets could be socio-demographics skewed, with a process chain inadvertently encoding biases, thus not representative of the broader population."
  ]
}